docs.snippet: Once known for its disappearing messages, Snap, the parent of Snapchat, has moved into news and, with Spectacles, consumer devices.

headline.main: While We Weren’t Looking, Snapchat Revolutionized Social Networks

docs.abstract: Farhad Manjoo State of the Art column marvels how Snap Inc has become one of world's most innovative and influential consumer technology companies despite perception that its Snapchat app is frivolous; notes firm's groundbreaking idea to make messages disappear after certain amount of time eliminates users seeking likes, follows and reshares, factors that have led to spread of fake news.

docs.snippet: The 12-minute orchestral work Stravinsky wrote at 26 was rediscovered in 2015. It will be performed in St. Petersburg, Russia.

headline.main: Second-Ever Concert of Stravinsky’s Lost ‘Funeral Song’ to Stream Free

docs.abstract: Funeral Song, recently rediscovered orchestral work by Igor Stravinsky, will be performed by Mariinsky Orchestra in St Petersburg and streamed online; piece has not been heard since its 1909 debut at memorial concert for Nikolai Rimsky-Korsakov.
